In this session we're going to take a
look at our first Ruby Data Structures.

00:00:05.952 --> 00:00:10.320
These data structures will allow us to
store more complex and interesting data.

00:00:11.320 --> 00:00:15.320
Up until this point we've seen how
we can use variables to store single

00:00:15.320 --> 00:00:16.700
pieces of data.

